---
title: Greek Salad Flatbreads with Artichokes, Olives, and Feta
description: Ah, the Greek salad. It’s one of those things that we don’t hesitate to order whenever we see it on a diner menu. The combo of lettuce, olives, feta, and veggies is a classic that can’t go wrong. With this recipe, though, we wanted to take the salad from reliable to radical, tossing its core ingredients on a flatbread and baking in the oven until warm, toasty, and bubbling with melted cheese.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/w17-r9-veggie-464caf3a.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/w17-r9-veggie-0b270447.pdf
time required: 25 minutes
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/greek-salad-flatbreads-58c2d8f2c6243b3874507bd3
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 60 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1540 mg
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees. Rinse and drain
@artichokes{1%jar}, then cut into halves through stems. Cut @green olives{1%oz}
and @grape tomatoes{4%oz} in half lengthwise. Halve, peel, and thinly slice
@red onion{1}. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}.

Tear the @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into small pieces.

Place @flatbreads{2} on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Scatter mozzarella,
olives, artichokes, tomatoes, and @feta cheese{1/2%cup} over each. Top with as
much onion and garlic as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Bake flatbreads in oven until crust is crisp and mozzarella is melted,
~{7-10%minutes}.

Toss @arugula{2%oz} in a #medium bowl{} with a @balsamic vinegar{1%tbsp} and a
drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Scatter arugula over flatbreads, then cut into slices and serve.

> The combo of lettuce, olives, feta, and veggies is a classic that can't go
> wrong. This recipe takes it from reliable to radical, topping flatbread with
> Greek salad ingredients and baking until warm, toasty, and bubbling with
> melted cheese.